, their marriage foundered, and the couple divorced in 1960. The couple stopped making weekly I Love Lucy shows in 1957. Her split-second timing, wide-mouthed wails and exaggerated pratfalls made the I Love Lucy show one of the most popular in television history. Miss Ball and her late former husband, Desi Arnaz, starred in I Love Lucy from 1951 to 1957 and have been seen since in widely syndicated reruns. She was Lucy and she was loved. She was 77. 